background: A audio company makes two types of headphones: wired headphones and wireless headphones.
constraints: Number of wired headphones is an integer
Number of wireless headphones is an integer
Number of wired headphones is non-negative
Number of wireless headphones is non-negative
The wired team can make at most MaxWired wired headphones per day
The wireless team can make at most MaxWireless wireless headphones per day
The audio testing machine can be used for at most MaxTesting headphones per day
objective: The company wants to maximize its profit, which is ProfitWired per wired headphone plus ProfitWireless per wireless headphone
description: A audio company make two types of headphones: wired headphones and wireless headphones. Two different teams make each type of headphones. The wired team can make at most \var{MaxWired} wired headphones per day and the wireless team can make at most \var{MaxWireless} wireless headphones per day. Both teams require use of a shared audio testing machine, and this machine can be used to make a maximum of \var{MaxTesting} headphones per day. The profit per wired headphone is \var{ProfitWired} and the profit per wireless headphone \var{ProfitWireless}. How many of each headphone should be made to maximize profit?

parameters.definition: Maximum number of wired headphones that can be produced per day by the wired team
Maximum number of wireless headphones that can be produced per day by the wireless team
Maximum capacity of shared audio testing machine per day
